# Routing and Pages Guide

## Page Structure
Pages are created in `src/pages/` and follow Astro's file-based routing:

- `index.astro` → `/`
- `about.astro` → `/about`
- `blog/[slug].astro` → `/blog/:slug`

## Dynamic Routes
Use square brackets for dynamic parameters:
```astro
---
// src/pages/blog/[slug].astro
const { slug } = Astro.params;
---
```

## Layout System
- Base layouts in `src/layouts/`
- Use `<slot />` for content injection
- Example:
```astro
---
// src/layouts/Layout.astro
interface Props {
  title: string;
}
const { title } = Astro.props;
---
<html>
  <head>
    <title>{title}</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <slot />
  </body>
</html>
```

## Static Assets
- Place in `public/` directory
- Reference directly in HTML:
```html
<img src="/images/logo.png" />
```

## Best Practices
1. Use consistent layout patterns
2. Keep routes organized by feature
3. Use TypeScript for route parameters
4. Implement proper meta tags
5. Follow SEO best practices
